{"snp3.8":{"snp3.8:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 3.8 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 3.8 ","html":"<article id='snp3.8'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp3.8:0.2":{"pli":"Sallasutta ","eng":"The Dart ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp3.8:1.1":{"pli":"Animittamanaññātaṃ, ","eng":"Unforeseen and unknown ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"A <i lang='pi' translate='no'>nimitta</i> is a sign or portent, and is commonly used in the context of omens, prophecy, or fortune-telling. Here it means that there is no portent or omen by which one can predict the extent of life. "},"snp3.8:1.2":{"pli":"maccānaṃ idha jīvitaṃ; ","eng":"is the extent of this mortal life—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:1.3":{"pli":"Kasirañca parittañca, ","eng":"hard and short ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:1.4":{"pli":"tañca dukkhena saṃyutaṃ. ","eng":"and bound to pain. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:2.1":{"pli":"Na hi so upakkamo atthi, ","eng":"There is no way that ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:2.2":{"pli":"yena jātā na miyyare; ","eng":"those born will not die. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:2.3":{"pli":"Jarampi patvā maraṇaṃ, ","eng":"On reaching old age death follows: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:2.4":{"pli":"evaṃdhammā hi pāṇino. ","eng":"such is the nature of living creatures. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:3.1":{"pli":"Phalānamiva pakkānaṃ, ","eng":"As ripe fruit ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:3.2":{"pli":"pāto patanato bhayaṃ; ","eng":"are always in danger of falling, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Accepting <i lang='pi' translate='no'>niccaṁ</i> per Norman and Bodhi. "},"snp3.8:3.3":{"pli":"Evaṃ jātāna maccānaṃ, ","eng":"so mortals once born ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:3.4":{"pli":"niccaṃ maraṇato bhayaṃ. ","eng":"are always in danger of death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:4.1":{"pli":"Yathāpi kumbhakārassa, ","eng":"As clay pots ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:4.2":{"pli":"katā mattikabhājanā; ","eng":"made by a potter ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:4.3":{"pli":"Sabbe bhedanapariyantā, ","eng":"all end up being broken, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:4.4":{"pli":"evaṃ maccāna jīvitaṃ. ","eng":"so is the life of mortals. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:5.1":{"pli":"Daharā ca mahantā ca, ","eng":"Young and old, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:5.2":{"pli":"ye bālā ye ca paṇḍitā; ","eng":"foolish and wise—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:5.3":{"pli":"Sabbe maccuvasaṃ yanti, ","eng":"all go under the sway of death; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:5.4":{"pli":"sabbe maccuparāyaṇā. ","eng":"all are destined to die. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:6.1":{"pli":"Tesaṃ maccuparetānaṃ, ","eng":"When those overcome by death ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:6.2":{"pli":"gacchataṃ paralokato; ","eng":"leave this world for the next, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:6.3":{"pli":"Na pitā tāyate puttaṃ, ","eng":"a father cannot protect his son, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:6.4":{"pli":"ñātī vā pana ñātake. ","eng":"nor relatives their kin. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:7.1":{"pli":"Pekkhataṃyeva ñātīnaṃ, ","eng":"See how, while relatives look on, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:7.2":{"pli":"passa lālapataṃ puthu; ","eng":"wailing profusely, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:7.3":{"pli":"Ekamekova maccānaṃ, ","eng":"mortals are led away one by one, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:7.4":{"pli":"govajjho viya nīyati. ","eng":"like a cow to the slaughter. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:8.1":{"pli":"Evamabbhāhato loko, ","eng":"And so the world is stricken ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:8.2":{"pli":"Maccunā ca jarāya ca; ","eng":"by old age and by death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:8.3":{"pli":"Tasmā dhīrā na socanti, ","eng":"That is why the attentive do not grieve, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:8.4":{"pli":"Viditvā lokapariyāyaṃ. ","eng":"for they understand the way of the world. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:9.1":{"pli":"Yassa maggaṃ na jānāsi, ","eng":"For one whose path you do not know—","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:9.2":{"pli":"āgatassa gatassa vā; ","eng":"not whence they came nor where they went—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:9.3":{"pli":"Ubho ante asampassaṃ, ","eng":"you lament in vain, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:9.4":{"pli":"niratthaṃ paridevasi. ","eng":"seeing neither end. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:10.1":{"pli":"Paridevayamāno ce, ","eng":"If a bewildered person, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:10.2":{"pli":"Kiñcidatthaṃ udabbahe; ","eng":"lamenting and self-harming, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:10.3":{"pli":"Sammūḷho hiṃsamattānaṃ, ","eng":"could extract any good from that, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:10.4":{"pli":"Kayirā ce naṃ vicakkhaṇo. ","eng":"then those who see clearly would do the same. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:11.1":{"pli":"Na hi ruṇṇena sokena, ","eng":"For not by weeping and wailing ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:11.2":{"pli":"Santiṃ pappoti cetaso; ","eng":"will you find peace of heart. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:11.3":{"pli":"Bhiyyassuppajjate dukkhaṃ, ","eng":"It just gives rise to more suffering, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:11.4":{"pli":"Sarīraṃ cupahaññati. ","eng":"and distresses your body. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:12.1":{"pli":"Kiso vivaṇṇo bhavati, ","eng":"Growing thin and pale, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:12.2":{"pli":"Hiṃsamattānamattanā; ","eng":"you hurt yourself. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:12.3":{"pli":"Na tena petā pālenti, ","eng":"It does nothing to help the dead: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:12.4":{"pli":"Niratthā paridevanā. ","eng":"your lamentation is in vain. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:13.1":{"pli":"Sokamappajahaṃ jantu, ","eng":"Unless a personage gives up grief, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:13.2":{"pli":"Bhiyyo dukkhaṃ nigacchati; ","eng":"they fall into suffering all the more. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:13.3":{"pli":"Anutthunanto kālaṅkataṃ, ","eng":"Bewailing those whose time has come, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:13.4":{"pli":"Sokassa vasamanvagū. ","eng":"you fall under the sway of grief. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:14.1":{"pli":"Aññepi passa gamine, ","eng":"See, too, other folk departing, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:14.2":{"pli":"Yathākammupage nare; ","eng":"passing on according to their deeds; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:14.3":{"pli":"Maccuno vasamāgamma, ","eng":"fallen under the sway of death, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:14.4":{"pli":"Phandantevidha pāṇino. ","eng":"beings flounder while still here. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:15.1":{"pli":"Yena yena hi maññanti, ","eng":"For whatever you imagine it is, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:15.2":{"pli":"Tato taṃ hoti aññathā; ","eng":"it turns out to be something else. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:15.3":{"pli":"Etādiso vinābhāvo, ","eng":"Such is separation: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:15.4":{"pli":"Passa lokassa pariyāyaṃ. ","eng":"see the way of the world! ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:16.1":{"pli":"Api vassasataṃ jīve, ","eng":"Even if a human lives ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:16.2":{"pli":"Bhiyyo vā pana māṇavo; ","eng":"a hundred years or more, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:16.3":{"pli":"Ñātisaṅghā vinā hoti, ","eng":"they are parted from their family circle, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:16.4":{"pli":"Jahāti idha jīvitaṃ. ","eng":"they leave this life behind. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:17.1":{"pli":"Tasmā arahato sutvā, ","eng":"Therefore, having learned from the Perfected One, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:17.2":{"pli":"Vineyya paridevitaṃ; ","eng":"dispel lamentation. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:17.3":{"pli":"Petaṃ kālaṅkataṃ disvā, ","eng":"Seeing the dead and departed, think: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:17.4":{"pli":"Neso labbhā mayā iti. ","eng":"“I cannot escape this.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"The commentary says this means, “I cannot bring back the dead”, which is followed by Norman and Bodhi. But I think the text elides a second negative and should read: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>na eso alabbhā</i>, literally “This is not not-to-be-gotten by me”, i.e. “I cannot escape this”. "},"snp3.8:18.1":{"pli":"Yathā saraṇamādittaṃ, ","eng":"As one would extinguish ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:18.2":{"pli":"Vārinā parinibbaye; ","eng":"a blazing refuge with water, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:18.3":{"pli":"Evampi dhīro sapañño, ","eng":"so too an attentive one—a wise, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:18.4":{"pli":"Paṇḍito kusalo naro; ","eng":"astute, and skilled person—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:18.5":{"pli":"Khippamuppatitaṃ sokaṃ, ","eng":"would swiftly blow away grief that comes up, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:18.6":{"pli":"Vāto tūlaṃva dhaṃsaye. ","eng":"like the wind a tuft of cotton. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:19.1":{"pli":"Paridevaṃ pajappañca, ","eng":"One who seeks their own happiness ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:19.2":{"pli":"Domanassañca attano; ","eng":"would pluck out the dart from themselves—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:19.3":{"pli":"Attano sukhamesāno, ","eng":"the wailing and moaning, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:19.4":{"pli":"Abbahe sallamattano. ","eng":"and sadness inside. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp3.8:20.1":{"pli":"Abbūḷhasallo asito, ","eng":"With dart plucked out, unattached, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:20.2":{"pli":"santiṃ pappuyya cetaso; ","eng":"having found peace of mind, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:20.3":{"pli":"Sabbasokaṃ atikkanto, ","eng":"overcoming all sorrow, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp3.8:20.4":{"pli":"asoko hoti nibbutoti. ","eng":"one is sorrowless and quenched. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp3.8:20.5":{"pli":"Sallasuttaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}}}